    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a benchmark 2002 BMW M3 Coupe, showcasing the pinnacle of the E46 chassis. This S54-powered specimen features a 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six with individual throttle bodies, maintaining factory-spec valve clearances and a fully serviced dual-VANOS system. Power is transmitted through a Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox to a limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The vehicle has undergone a preventative subframe reinforcement to guarantee structural rigidity under high lateral loads. The suspension geometry remains true, with no bushing deflection or damper leakage. Finished in its original pigment with high-gloss retention and zero oxidation, the cockpit preserves its Nappa leather bolsters and functional pixel-perfect instrumentation. This is a mechanically synchronized, collector-grade example with no deferred maintenance.",
